The paper discusses the properties and applications of Euclidean distance matrices (EDMs), which are commonly used in machine learning, wireless sensor networks, and acoustics. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Signal Processing (cs.SI), Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD), or Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-categories. However, since the paper focuses on the mathematical properties and algorithms related to EDMs, it is most likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The other sub-categories are also possible, but less likely, as they are more application-specific.
